# Getting started: Using a pre-trained network for segmenting an epithelium 

This is a quick tutorial that show how one can use our pre-trained convolutional neural network (CNN) to segment epithelia

## Pre-requisites

- **Place** the **images** to be segmented in a **folder named 'unseen'**  

## Load the pre-trained model

- Go to the **'Model' tab**
- In the 'Model' box, select **'Use a pre-trained model'**

<img src="data:image/png;base64, " />

![](./15.png?raw=true "Optional Title")

- Press **'Go'** at the bottom of current tab **to load the model**

<img src="data:image/png;base64, " />

![](./16.png?raw=true "Optional Title")

## Predict epithelia segmentation

- Go to the **'Predict'** tab
- **Drag & Drop** your 'unseen' folder onto the 'Dataset' field

<img src="data:image/png;base64, " />

![](./17.png?raw=true "Optional Title")

- In **'Channel number adjustment'** select the 'Channel of interest' if your input has several channels (a preview of the channel is available below)

<img src="data:image/png;base64, " />

![](./18.png?raw=true "Optional Title")

- Press **'Go (predict)'** at the bottom of the tab and wait a few seconds/minutes
- Browse your 'unseen' folder, EPySeg predictions can be found in a folder named **'predict'**.

**PS:** if you are **not happy** with the results, first try **tuning the 'score' parameter**. If nothing works, you can try re-training the model with your own dataset.

<img src="data:image/png;base64, " />

![](./19.png?raw=true "Optional Title")
